  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are various legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Approaches:\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering activities\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures:\n- Customer identification requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Enhanced due diligence for high-risk clients\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n- Government regulatory agencies\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure and financial penalties\n\n5. Global Cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- International law enforcement collaboration\n- Coordinated investigation strategies\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
